699
01:11:13,829 --> 01:11:15,659
你是怎麼這樣受傷的？
{\fs12}How did you hurt it like this?{\r}

700
01:11:15,779 --> 01:11:19,216
好吧，我和桑德去了這個監獄，尋找我的爸爸。
{\fs12}Well, me and Sounder went to this prison camp looking for my daddy.{\r}

701
01:11:19,336 --> 01:11:21,493
守衛打我的手。
{\fs12}And the guard hit me on my hand.{\r}

702
01:11:22,639 --> 01:11:26,719
 -你母親知道你會去見你父親嗎？ -是的女士。
{\fs12}-Did your mother know you were going to see your father? -Yes, ma'am.{\r}

703
01:11:29,011 --> 01:11:30,164
這樣做。
{\fs12}That does it.{\r}

704
01:11:30,948 --> 01:11:32,436
謝謝，約翰遜女士。
{\fs12}Thanks, Ms. Johnson.{\r}

705
01:11:33,099 --> 01:11:34,446
大衛？
{\fs12}David?{\r}

706
01:11:35,029 --> 01:11:39,063
為什麼不在學校結束之前留下來？我離這兒不遠。
{\fs12}Why don't you stay until school is over? I don't live far from here.{\r}

707
01:11:39,183 --> 01:11:43,384
你和你的狗可以和我一起回家，讓自己吃一頓熱飯。
{\fs12}You and your dog can come home with me and have yourselves a hot meal.{\r}

708
01:11:44,455 --> 01:11:47,430
然後我們可以談談如何讓你回家。
{\fs12}Then we can talk about how to get you back home.{\r}

709
01:11:49,822 --> 01:11:51,330
是的女士。
{\fs12}Yes, ma'am.{\r}

710
01:11:52,642 --> 01:11:54,680
在那裡坐下。
{\fs12}Take a seat back there.{\r}

711
01:12:36,492 --> 01:12:37,859
留下來，桑德。
{\fs12}Stay, Sounder.{\r}

712
01:13:06,677 --> 01:13:09,109
約翰遜女士，你有一個漂亮的房子！
{\fs12}You've got a pretty house, Ms. Johnson!{\r}

713
01:13:09,229 --> 01:13:10,415
我試試。
{\fs12}I try.{\r}

714
01:13:13,650 --> 01:13:16,143
你也有很多書。
{\fs12}You've got a lot of books, too.{\r}

715
01:13:19,624 --> 01:13:23,382
這裡。讓我告訴你這些書架上的書籍。
{\fs12}Here. Let me tell you something about the books on these shelves.{\r}

716
01:13:24,508 --> 01:13:28,636
這本書是關於一個幫助解放奴隸的女人。她叫Harriet Tubman。
{\fs12}This book is about a woman who helped to free slaves. Her name is Harriet Tubman.{\r}

717
01:13:28,756 --> 01:13:30,767
她於1915年去世。
{\fs12}She died in 1915.{\r}

718
01:13:31,909 --> 01:13:33,460
謝謝，約翰遜女士。
{\fs12}Thanks, Ms. Johnson.{\r}

719
01:13:34,601 --> 01:13:37,958
這個是關於一個名叫Crispus Attucks的人。
{\fs12}And this one is about a man called Crispus Attucks.{\r}

720
01:13:38,078 --> 01:13:40,952
他是第一個在美國革命中死去的黑人。
{\fs12}He was the first black man to die in the American Revolution.{\r}

721
01:13:41,072 --> 01:13:45,190
為幫助這個國家而戰的戰爭成為了美國。
{\fs12}The war that was fought to help this country become the United States.{\r}

722
01:13:48,024 --> 01:13:49,611
約翰遜女士？
{\fs12}Ms. Johnson?{\r}

723
01:13:49,731 --> 01:13:53,049
難道你不在你的學校教導沒有死的人嗎？
{\fs12}Don't you teach in your school about folk who ain't dead?{\r}

724
01:13:53,169 --> 01:13:54,415
當然！
{\fs12}Sure!{\r}

725
01:13:56,345 --> 01:13:59,179
這是關於一個非常活躍的男人的一個。
{\fs12}Here's one about a man who's very much alive.{\r}

726
01:13:59,973 --> 01:14:01,782
William E.B.博士杜波依斯。
{\fs12}Dr. William E.B. DuBois.{\r}

727
01:14:01,902 --> 01:14:05,912
 -他在說什麼？ -在這裡，我會讀到他說的話：
{\fs12}-What does he talk about?   -Here, I'll read something he said:{\r}

728
01:14:10,364 --> 01:14:13,338
“[...]黑人的渴望必須得到尊重：”
{\fs12}"[...] the longing of black men must have respect:"{\r}

729
01:14:14,283 --> 01:14:17,660
（這意味著男人和女人都是人，必須以這種方式對待。）
{\fs12}(Which means that a man, and a woman, are human and must be treated that way.){\r}

730
01:14:18,261 --> 01:14:20,801
“...豐富而深刻的經歷...”
{\fs12}"...the rich and bitter depth of their experience..."{\r}

731
01:14:20,921 --> 01:14:23,595
“...他們內心生活的未知寶藏...”
{\fs12}"...the unknown treasures of their inner life..."{\r}

732
01:14:23,715 --> 01:14:26,751
“...他們看到的大自然的奇怪贖罪...”
{\fs12}"...the strange rendings of nature they have seen..."{\r}

733
01:14:26,871 --> 01:14:29,367
“...可能會給全世界帶來新的觀點...”
{\fs12}"...may give the world new points of view..."{\r}

734
01:14:29,487 --> 01:14:34,663
“...讓他們的愛，生活和行為，對所有人的心靈都是珍貴的。”

{\fs12}"...and make their loving, living, and doing, precious to all human hearts."{\r}

735
01:14:34,783 --> 01:14:39,012
“在這些嘗試靈魂的日子裡，自己...”
{\fs12}"And to themselves in these the days that try their souls..."{\r}

736
01:14:39,132 --> 01:14:42,323
“...在煙霧瀰漫的昏暗藍色空氣中翱翔的機會...”
{\fs12}"...the chance to soar in the dim blue air above the smoke..."{\r}

737
01:14:42,443 --> 01:14:44,273
“...對他們更好的精神...”
{\fs12}"...is to their finer spirits..."{\r}

738
01:14:44,393 --> 01:14:48,394
“...因為他們在黑暗中失去了地球上所失去的東西。”
{\fs12}"...boon and guerdon for what they lose on earth by being black."{\r}

739
01:14:48,514 --> 01:14:51,529
<i> [來自黑人靈魂，第6章] </ i>
{\fs12}[from The Souls of Black Men, Chapter 6]{\r}

740
01:14:53,358 --> 01:14:55,750
約翰遜女士，你是個好女人。
{\fs12}You're a nice lady, Ms. Johnson.{\r}

741
01:15:01,409 --> 01:15:04,130
好的。好的。
{\fs12}Alright. Alright.{\r}

742
01:15:04,894 --> 01:15:06,723
讓我們停止笑。
{\fs12}Let's stop the laughing.{\r}

743
01:15:06,843 --> 01:15:08,492
還有誰有故事告訴我們？
{\fs12}Who else has a story to tell us?{\r}

744
01:15:09,417 --> 01:15:13,290
我有一個故事，約翰遜女士。一個發生在我身上的真實故事。
{\fs12}I got a story, Ms. Johnson. A true story that happened to me.{\r}

745
01:15:14,088 --> 01:15:17,304
克拉倫斯，你知道課程會挑戰你的故事，不是嗎？
{\fs12}You know the class is going to challenge your story, don't you, Clarence?{\r}

746
01:15:17,424 --> 01:15:19,142
是的，約翰遜女士。
{\fs12}Yes, Ms. Johnson.{\r}

747
01:15:19,262 --> 01:15:20,810
好的，繼續。
{\fs12}Alright, go on.{\r}

748
01:15:22,719 --> 01:15:25,885
我和我的妹妹上週六去了水洞。
{\fs12}Me and my little sister went down to the water hole last Saturday.{\r}

749
01:15:26,005 --> 01:15:30,619
你們都做錯了什麼。你沒告訴我們你妹妹的名字。
{\fs12}You all was doing something wrong. You didn't tell us the name of your sister.{\r}

750
01:15:30,739 --> 01:15:34,807
我和我的妹妹勞拉上週六去了水洞。
{\fs12}Me and my sister Laura went down to the water hole last Saturday.{\r}

751
01:15:34,927 --> 01:15:37,360
我們沿著水邊玩耍。
{\fs12}We was playing along the edge of the water.{\r}

752
01:15:37,480 --> 01:15:39,691
勞拉滑倒了，掉進了水里。
{\fs12}Laura slipped and fell into the water.{\r}

753
01:15:39,811 --> 01:15:44,850
我開始跑回家了。但我轉身，跑回去，潛入水中...
{\fs12}I started to run back home. But I turned around, ran back, dove into the water...{\r}

754
01:15:44,970 --> 01:15:47,443
...在她淹死之前讓她出去了。
{\fs12}...and got her out before she could drown.{\r}

755
01:15:47,563 --> 01:15:50,114
在你把她從水里拉出來之後，你妹妹怎麼樣？
{\fs12}How was your sister after you pulled her out of the water?{\r}

756
01:15:50,234 --> 01:15:52,224
她又髒又濕。
{\fs12}She was dirty and wet.{\r}

757
01:15:52,344 --> 01:15:53,752
是什麼讓你跑？
{\fs12}What made you run?{\r}

758
01:15:53,872 --> 01:15:56,124
我回家去找我爸爸。
{\fs12}I was going home to get my daddy.{\r}

759
01:15:56,244 --> 01:15:58,335
是什麼讓你停下來回去？
{\fs12}What made you stop and go back?{\r}

760
01:15:58,455 --> 01:16:00,222
因為如果我跑回家...
{\fs12}Cause if I had ran home...{\r}

761
01:16:00,342 --> 01:16:03,458
...當我應該回來的時候，我妹妹會淹死。
{\fs12}...by the time I should have got back, my sister would have drowned.{\r}

762
01:16:03,578 --> 01:16:05,951
你怎麼一開始不知道的？
{\fs12}How come you didn't know that at first?{\r}

763
01:16:06,071 --> 01:16:07,199
因為我很害怕。
{\fs12}Cause I was scared.{\r}

764
01:16:07,319 --> 01:16:10,476
拿著它！克拉倫斯的故事並非如此。
{\fs12}Hold it! Clarence's story ain't true.{\r}

765
01:16:10,958 --> 01:16:15,541
我和克拉倫斯很多次去過河邊，我知道他不會游泳！
{\fs12}Me and Clarence went to the river a lot of times, and I know he can't swim!{\r}

766
01:16:23,304 --> 01:16:27,887
克拉倫斯？在告訴我們之後，你能告訴我們一個不真實的故事嗎？
{\fs12}Clarence? Would you tell us a story that was not true, after telling us it was?{\r}

767
01:16:28,422 --> 01:16:30,030
不，約翰遜女士。
{\fs12}No, Ms. Johnson.{\r}

768
01:16:30,150 --> 01:16:31,438
你會游泳嗎？
{\fs12}Can you swim?{\r}

769
01:16:31,558 --> 01:16:32,503
是的女士。
{\fs12}Yes, ma'am.{\r}

770
01:16:32,623 --> 01:16:36,863
克拉倫斯！你知道你不會游泳。里奇先生每次都向你展示...
{\fs12}Clarence! You know you can't swim. Every time Mr. Richie showed you...{\r}

771
01:16:36,983 --> 01:16:40,254
你摔倒了我不得不一直把你拉出來。
{\fs12}...you fell down. And I had to always pull you out.{\r}

772
01:16:45,034 --> 01:16:46,401
是的女士。
{\fs12}Yes, ma'am.{\r}

773
01:16:46,521 --> 01:16:50,561
但是，當我看到我的妹妹即將被淹死在水中時...
{\fs12}But when I saw my sister about to drown in the water...{\r}

774
01:16:50,681 --> 01:16:53,657
我試過了，因為我不再害怕了。
{\fs12}I tried, because I wasn't scared anymore.{\r}

775
01:16:53,777 --> 01:16:58,172
我只是游泳和踢。我不知道我是怎麼做的，但我是。
{\fs12}I was just swimming and kicking. I don't know how I was doing it, but I was.{\r}

776
01:16:58,292 --> 01:17:01,488
因為我姐姐溺水了。她溺水了！
{\fs12}Because my sister was drowning. She was drowning!{\r}

777
01:17:03,197 --> 01:17:05,680
我相信克拉倫斯的故事。
{\fs12}I believe Clarence's story.{\r}

778
01:17:05,800 --> 01:17:08,735
大衛，你想站起來告訴我們原因嗎？
{\fs12}Do you want to stand up and tell us why, David?{\r}

779
01:17:11,957 --> 01:17:15,314
嗯...有些人來找我父親。
{\fs12}Well...some people came and took my father away.{\r}

780
01:17:15,757 --> 01:17:19,938
其他人說我們無法在農場工作。但我們必須這樣做。
{\fs12}And other people said we couldn't work the farm. But we had to.{\r}

781
01:17:20,058 --> 01:17:22,450
否則我們會失去農場。
{\fs12}Or else we would have lost the farm.{\r}

782
01:17:22,570 --> 01:17:25,666
但我們種植了莊稼並且他們長大了。
{\fs12}But we planted the crops and they grew.{\r}

783
01:17:25,786 --> 01:17:28,809
我相信克拉倫斯的故事是因為他做了什麼。
{\fs12}I believe Clarence's story because of what he did.{\r}

784
01:17:28,929 --> 01:17:33,352
他不會游泳，但他不得不游泳！否則他的妹妹會被淹死！
{\fs12}He couldn't swim, but he had to! Else his sister would have drowned!{\r}

785
01:17:36,627 --> 01:17:38,617
這就是他如何做到的。
{\fs12}And that's how he did it.{\r}

786
01:17:55,017 --> 01:17:58,977
你知道，這是你今天在課堂上為克拉倫斯所做的一件好事。
{\fs12}You know, that was a good thing you did for Clarence in class today.{\r}

787
01:17:59,097 --> 01:18:00,806
我相信他的故事。
{\fs12}I believed his story.{\r}

788
01:18:00,926 --> 01:18:03,734
但我害怕其他孩子不會。
{\fs12}But I was afraid the other children wouldn't.{\r}

789
01:18:04,336 --> 01:18:08,156
我知道他害怕一站起來就沒有人會相信他。
{\fs12}I knew he was scared nobody would believe him as soon as he stood up.{\r}

790
01:18:08,276 --> 01:18:10,507
你呢？怎麼樣？
{\fs12}You did? How?{\r}

791
01:18:10,627 --> 01:18:13,055
我自己一直都喜歡這樣。
{\fs12}I've been like that sometimes, myself.{\r}

792
01:18:13,175 --> 01:18:15,387
以為沒有人會相信我。
{\fs12}Thinking nobody would believe me.{\r}

793
01:18:17,258 --> 01:18:19,952
 -你想听另一個故事嗎？ -不是現在，大衛。
{\fs12}-You want to hear another story? -Not now, David.{\r}

794
01:18:20,072 --> 01:18:24,253
現在已經很晚了，你早上還有很長一段路程。
{\fs12}It's getting late and you have a long trip ahead of you in the morning.{\r}

795
01:18:45,826 --> 01:18:49,130
那你在看什麼？沒什麼好看的。
{\fs12}What are you looking at out there? There's nothing to see.{\r}

796
01:18:49,250 --> 01:18:51,703
爸爸總是眺望黑暗。
{\fs12}Daddy always looks out into the dark.{\r}

797
01:18:52,928 --> 01:18:55,119
即使沒有什麼可看的。
{\fs12}Even when there's nothing to see.{\r}

798
01:18:55,441 --> 01:18:57,310
他說這是你聽到的。
{\fs12}He says it's what you hear.{\r}

799
01:18:57,430 --> 01:18:59,651
你想想你的父親很多，不是嗎？
{\fs12}You think about your father a lot, don't you?{\r}

800
01:18:59,771 --> 01:19:00,938
是的女士。
{\fs12}Yes, ma'am.{\r}

801
01:19:01,761 --> 01:19:04,746
大衛，你不應該太擔心他。
{\fs12}You shouldn't worry about him too much, David.{\r}

802
01:19:06,072 --> 01:19:09,096
但是當我回到家時，我會告訴媽媽什麼？
{\fs12}But what am I going to tell Mama when I get home?{\r}

803
01:19:09,398 --> 01:19:13,478
告訴她我沒看到爸爸？這就是我想要做的！
{\fs12}Tell her that I didn't see Daddy? And that's what I wanted to do!{\r}

804
01:19:13,598 --> 01:19:15,609
但你盡力而為。
{\fs12}But you did all you could.{\r}

805
01:19:15,729 --> 01:19:18,422
沒有多少小男孩可以像你一樣去過這樣的旅程。
{\fs12}Not many little boys could have gone on such a journey as you did.{\r}

806
01:19:18,542 --> 01:19:20,091
但是爸爸在哪裡？
{\fs12}But where's Daddy?{\r}

807
01:19:22,179 --> 01:19:24,069
我無法回答你的問題。
{\fs12}I can't answer that for you.{\r}

808
01:19:24,631 --> 01:19:28,832
但是，你不知道你父親在哪裡，這不是你自己的錯。
{\fs12}But it's no fault of your own that you don't know where your father is.{\r}

809
01:19:28,952 --> 01:19:32,197
告訴我你做了什麼讓你無法找到你的父親。
{\fs12}Tell me what you did that kept you from finding your father.{\r}

810
01:19:32,317 --> 01:19:34,308
嗯？拜託告訴我！
{\fs12}Hmm? Come on, tell me!{\r}

811
01:19:34,428 --> 01:19:35,654
沒有。
{\fs12}Nothing.{\r}

812
01:19:35,774 --> 01:19:37,885
所以你做了你的工作，對嗎？
{\fs12}And so you did your job, right?{\r}

813
01:19:39,637 --> 01:19:41,044
是的女士。
{\fs12}Yes, ma'am.{\r}

814
01:19:42,311 --> 01:19:45,627
男孩...你肯定會讓我的思緒跳躍！
{\fs12}Boy...you sure keep my mind jumping!{\r}

815
01:19:46,638 --> 01:19:48,682
這意味著什麼？
{\fs12}And what does that mean?{\r}

816
01:19:48,802 --> 01:19:52,349
這意味著你讓我用我的頭，這很好。
{\fs12}That means you keep me using my head, and that's good.{\r}

817
01:19:53,113 --> 01:19:54,600
約翰遜女士？
{\fs12}Ms. Johnson?{\r}

818
01:19:56,697 --> 01:20:02,366
你以為我可以回到這裡...與其他孩子一起上學？
{\fs12}You think I can come back here and... study school with the other children?{\r}

819
01:20:31,523 --> 01:20:32,927
滿了嗎？
{\fs12}Full yet?{\r}

820
01:20:33,232 --> 01:20:34,155
精細。
{\fs12}Fine.{\r}

821
01:20:34,275 --> 01:20:36,901
媽媽，媽媽！喬西梅！厄爾！
{\fs12}Mama, mama! Josie Mae! Earl!{\r}

822
01:20:38,377 --> 01:20:39,893
 -大衛李！ -大衛李！
{\fs12}-David Lee! -David Lee!{\r}

823
01:20:41,857 --> 01:20:43,010
大衛李？
{\fs12}David Lee?{\r}

824
01:20:45,498 --> 01:20:46,822
大衛李？
{\fs12}David Lee?{\r}

825
01:20:47,569 --> 01:20:51,266
主啊，男孩，你去過哪裡？你讓我擔心我的想法！
{\fs12}Lord, boy, where have you been? You had me worried out of my mind!{\r}

826
01:20:51,386 --> 01:20:53,359
你找到你的爸爸？
{\fs12}You find your daddy?{\r}

827
01:20:53,479 --> 01:20:55,174
不，我沒有看到他。
{\fs12}No, I didn't see him.{\r}

828
01:20:55,294 --> 01:20:58,099
那些人說他們不認識爸爸。
{\fs12}The men said they didn't know Daddy.{\r}

829
01:20:58,219 --> 01:21:00,021
猜猜他們把他送到了另一個營地。
{\fs12}Guess they sent him off to another camp.{\r}

830
01:21:00,141 --> 01:21:02,694
為什麼你的包很重？那裡有什麼？
{\fs12}Why's your bag so heavy? What's in there?{\r}

831
01:21:02,814 --> 01:21:04,543
約翰遜女士給我的一些書。
{\fs12}Some books Ms. Johnson gave me.{\r}

832
01:21:04,663 --> 01:21:06,080
誰是約翰遜女士？
{\fs12}Who's Ms. Johnson?{\r}

833
01:21:06,200 --> 01:21:10,813
哦，她是老師。我有時候一直呆在她家裡。
{\fs12}Oh, she's a teacher. And I stayed over at her house some of the time.{\r}

834
01:21:10,933 --> 01:21:15,617
所以當我離開時，她給了我這些書。
{\fs12}So when I left, she gave me these books.{\r}

835
01:21:16,500 --> 01:21:17,674
好...
{\fs12}Well...{\r}

836
01:21:19,361 --> 01:21:22,006
約翰遜女士一定是個好女人。
{\fs12}Ms. Johnson must be a right nice lady.{\r}

837
01:21:22,126 --> 01:21:24,056
噢，她是，媽媽。
{\fs12}Oh, she is, Mama.{\r}

838
01:21:27,237 --> 01:21:28,689
媽媽...
{\fs12}Mama...{\r}

839
01:21:29,215 --> 01:21:33,015
秋天到來時，約翰遜女士要我去她的學校。
{\fs12}When the fall comes, Ms. Johnson wants me to go to her school.{\r}

840
01:21:37,115 --> 01:21:39,463
那你怎麼能這樣做？
{\fs12}Well, how can you do that?{\r}

841
01:21:40,530 --> 01:21:43,413
你不會住在那所學校附近。
{\fs12}You don't live nowhere near that school.{\r}

842
01:21:43,533 --> 01:21:46,680
好吧，她說我可以和學生一起生活。
{\fs12}Well, she says I can live with her while school's going on.{\r}

843
01:21:46,800 --> 01:21:50,092
當學校不能繼續學習時，我可以回家。
{\fs12}And when school's not going on, I could come back home.{\r}

844
01:21:54,191 --> 01:21:56,690
那麼，誰能在這裡幫助我呢？
{\fs12}Well, who's going to help me here in the house?{\r}

845
01:21:58,227 --> 01:22:00,213
在現場？
{\fs12}And in the field?{\r}

846
01:22:07,889 --> 01:22:09,085
好...
{\fs12}Well...{\r}

847
01:22:09,768 --> 01:22:12,438
也許到那個時候，你爸爸會回來的。
{\fs12}Maybe by that time, your dad will be back.{\r}

848
01:22:12,907 --> 01:22:15,982
如果和他一起好的話，對我來說也沒關係。
{\fs12}If it's alright with him, it's alright with me.{\r}

849
01:23:15,569 --> 01:23:18,409
Giddyup，騾子！混帳！混帳！混帳！混帳！
{\fs12}Giddyup, mule! Git! Git! Git! Git!{\r}

850
01:23:25,472 --> 01:23:26,454
是啊。
{\fs12}Yeah.{\r}

851
01:23:31,340 --> 01:23:33,006
這樣就完成了你的分享。
{\fs12}This finishes your share.{\r}

852
01:23:33,126 --> 01:23:35,568
麗貝卡，你做得很好。
{\fs12}You did a good job cropping, Rebecca.{\r}

853
01:23:46,909 --> 01:23:48,104
Giddyup，騾子！
{\fs12}Giddyup, mule!{\r}

854
01:24:08,826 --> 01:24:13,096
親愛的約翰遜女士，你好嗎？我做得很好。
{\fs12}Dear Ms. Johnson, How are you? I am doing OK.{\r}

855
01:24:13,216 --> 01:24:16,982
我告訴了我的媽媽，我的兄弟和我的妹妹。
{\fs12}I told my mama, my brother, and my sister about you.{\r}

856
01:24:17,446 --> 01:24:19,304
他們也喜歡你。
{\fs12}And they like you too.{\r}

857
01:24:19,424 --> 01:24:23,574
我不能把這封信寫得太長，因為我有工作要做。
{\fs12}I can't make this letter too long because I have work to do.{\r}

858
01:24:23,694 --> 01:24:26,798
祝福你，大衛李.摩根
{\fs12}Bless you, David Lee Morgan{\r}

859
01:24:28,492 --> 01:24:31,246
兒子，你肯定會寫一封很好的信。
{\fs12}You sure write a good fine letter, son.{\r}

860
01:24:32,714 --> 01:24:34,721
一封好的信。
{\fs12}A good fine letter.{\r}

861
01:24:58,755 --> 01:25:00,826
你怎麼了，桑德？
{\fs12}What's wrong with you, Sounder?{\r}

862
01:25:38,809 --> 01:25:40,410
哦，我的上帝。
{\fs12}Oh, my God.{\r}

863
01:25:41,819 --> 01:25:43,207
這是納森。
{\fs12}It's Nathan.{\r}

864
01:25:44,467 --> 01:25:45,808
這是納森。
{\fs12}Nathan!{\r}

865
01:25:48,267 --> 01:25:49,719
這是納森。
{\fs12}Nathan!{\r}

866
01:25:51,235 --> 01:25:53,050
媽媽！怎麼了？
{\fs12}Mama! What's the matter?{\r}

867
01:25:53,170 --> 01:25:54,416
納森！
{\fs12}Nathan!{\r}

868
01:25:58,021 --> 01:26:00,391
納森！納森。
{\fs12}Nathan! Nathan.{\r}

869
01:26:01,736 --> 01:26:02,734
爸爸！
{\fs12}Daddy!{\r}

870
01:26:02,854 --> 01:26:05,126
 -爸爸！ -爸爸！
{\fs12}-Daddy! -Daddy!{\r}

871
01:26:05,246 --> 01:26:07,218
 -爸爸！ -爸爸！ -納森！
{\fs12}-Daddy! -Daddy! -Nathan!{\r}

872
01:26:07,517 --> 01:26:09,674
 -爸爸！ -爸爸！
{\fs12}-Daddy! -Daddy!{\r}

873
01:26:09,977 --> 01:26:11,446
 -納森！ -爸爸！
{\fs12}-Nathan! -Daddy!{\r}

874
01:26:14,197 --> 01:26:15,457
爸爸！
{\fs12}Daddy!{\r}

875
01:26:15,937 --> 01:26:17,646
 -納森 -爸爸！
{\fs12}-Nathan. -Daddy!{\r}

876
01:26:22,510 --> 01:26:23,386
爸爸！
{\fs12}Daddy!{\r}

877
01:26:23,506 --> 01:26:24,902
 -爸爸！ -爸爸！
{\fs12}-Daddy! -Daddy!{\r}

878
01:26:25,713 --> 01:26:27,635
Rebec ...麗貝卡。
{\fs12}Rebec...Rebecca.{\r}

879
01:26:28,148 --> 01:26:29,109
爸爸！
{\fs12}Daddy!{\r}

880
01:26:37,291 --> 01:26:38,679
 -納森-嗯。
{\fs12}-Nathan. -Uh-huh.{\r}

881
01:26:44,083 --> 01:26:45,834
嘿!嘿!
{\fs12}Hey! Hey!{\r}

882
01:26:59,334 --> 01:27:01,405
很高興...看著你！
{\fs12}It's good to...look at you!{\r}

883
01:27:02,938 --> 01:27:03,963
嘿!
{\fs12}Hey!{\r}

884
01:27:09,664 --> 01:27:10,674
厄爾
{\fs12}Earl.{\r}

885
01:27:16,916 --> 01:27:19,265
你的腿怎麼了，爸爸？
{\fs12}What's the matter with your leg, Daddy?{\r}

886
01:27:19,385 --> 01:27:21,478
哦。我受傷了
{\fs12}Oh. I got it hurt.{\r}

887
01:27:22,302 --> 01:27:23,925
在炸藥爆炸。
{\fs12}In a dynamite blast.{\r}

888
01:27:24,045 --> 01:27:28,276
當我不再對他們有用時，他們花了一些時間來減刑...
{\fs12}When I wasn't no more use to them, they took some time off my sentence...{\r}

889
01:27:28,396 --> 01:27:30,354
...讓我回家吧！
{\fs12}...and let me come home!{\r}

890
01:27:34,338 --> 01:27:39,014
那是你給我們定的一頓飯，麗貝卡女士，我當然要謝謝你。
{\fs12}That was some meal you fixed for us, Ms. Rebecca, and I sure wanna thank you.{\r}

891
01:27:39,134 --> 01:27:41,529
好吧，我很高興你喜歡它，納森李！
{\fs12}Well, I'm glad you like it, Nathan Lee!{\r}

892
01:27:41,649 --> 01:27:44,476
你知道，我很想念他們的餃子，就像我想念你一樣，厄爾
{\fs12}You know, I missed them dumplings almost as much as I missed you, Earl.{\r}

893
01:27:46,512 --> 01:27:51,012
好吧，孩子，這是你睡前2小時。繼續前進。來吧！
{\fs12}Alright, children, it's 2 hours past your bedtime. Get a move on. Come on!{\r}

894
01:27:51,132 --> 01:27:52,092
你也是，厄爾
{\fs12}You too, Earl.{\r}

895
01:27:52,212 --> 01:27:53,902
晚安，爸爸。
{\fs12}Goodnight, Daddy.{\r}

896
01:27:54,022 --> 01:27:56,550
晚安，你這個小東西。
{\fs12}Goodnight, you pretty little thing you.{\r}

897
01:27:57,148 --> 01:27:58,621
晚安，爸爸。
{\fs12}Goodnight, Daddy.{\r}

898
01:27:59,933 --> 01:28:01,535
晚安回到你身邊。
{\fs12}Goodnight back at you.{\r}

899
01:28:07,055 --> 01:28:09,702
睡覺。脫鞋。你聽？
{\fs12}Go to bed. Take your shoes off. You hear?{\r}

900
01:28:09,822 --> 01:28:12,030
那是你繼續的一段旅程，男孩！
{\fs12}That was some journey you went on, boy!{\r}

901
01:28:13,289 --> 01:28:15,426
爸爸，我很高興你回家了。
{\fs12}Daddy, I'm so glad you're home.{\r}

902
01:28:15,725 --> 01:28:17,881
嗯...我也是，兒子！
{\fs12}Well...me too, son!{\r}

903
01:28:18,001 --> 01:28:19,611
我們再去打獵？
{\fs12}We going hunting again?{\r}

904
01:28:19,731 --> 01:28:22,195
好吧，我們肯定會再去打獵！
{\fs12}Well, sure we're going hunting again!{\r}

905
01:28:22,552 --> 01:28:25,776
你離開的時候我把你的東西清理乾淨了。
{\fs12}I cleaned and oiled your stuff while you was gone.{\r}

906
01:28:27,057 --> 01:28:29,769
 -很好 -你現在轉過來，大衛李。
{\fs12}-Good. -Your turn now, David Lee.{\r}

907
01:28:35,911 --> 01:28:37,342
晚安，爸爸。
{\fs12}Goodnight, Daddy.{\r}

908
01:28:38,431 --> 01:28:40,117
晚安，兒子。
{\fs12}Goodnight, son.{\r}

909
01:28:40,237 --> 01:28:42,263
爸爸，你現在回家了。這就是我想要的。
{\fs12}Daddy, you're home now. That's all I want.{\r}

910
01:28:42,383 --> 01:28:45,274
我不想要別的。只是你回家。
{\fs12}I don't want nothing else. Just you to be home.{\r}

911
01:28:47,668 --> 01:28:49,184
來吧，男孩。
{\fs12}Come here, boy.{\r}

912
01:29:55,833 --> 01:29:57,621
嗨，麗貝卡。
{\fs12}Hi-ya, Rebecca.{\r}

913
01:29:57,741 --> 01:29:58,753
你好。
{\fs12}Hi.{\r}

914
01:29:59,522 --> 01:30:02,233
有人告訴我納森回來了。他怎麼樣？
{\fs12}Somebody told me Nathan's back. How is he?{\r}

915
01:30:02,917 --> 01:30:06,913
帕金斯先生，你為什麼不拜訪他？他會告訴你他是怎麼回事。
{\fs12}Why don't you pay him a visit, Mr. Perkins? He'll tell you how he is.{\r}

916
01:30:07,276 --> 01:30:09,924
麗貝卡，我會那樣做的。我會這樣做的。
{\fs12}I'll do that, Rebecca. I'll do just that.{\r}

917
01:30:16,300 --> 01:30:18,573
那個老啄木鳥現在想要什麼？
{\fs12}What does that old peckerwood want now?{\r}

918
01:30:18,693 --> 01:30:20,203
好！
{\fs12}Well!{\r}

919
01:30:20,935 --> 01:30:23,028
他希望你拜訪他。
{\fs12}He wants you to pay him a visit.{\r}

920
01:30:27,147 --> 01:30:29,367
你們兩個可以坐在陰涼的樹下...
{\fs12}The two of you could sit under a shady tree...{\r}

921
01:30:29,487 --> 01:30:32,463
...喝冰冷的威士忌，拍攝微風！
{\fs12}...drink ice-cold whiskey, and shoot the breeze!{\r}

922
01:30:33,616 --> 01:30:37,625
嗯，我希望你告訴他我太忙了，不能那種東西。
{\fs12}Well, I hope you told him I was too busy for that kind of stuff.{\r}

923
01:30:43,165 --> 01:30:44,404
早安！
{\fs12}Good morning!{\r}

924
01:30:47,521 --> 01:30:48,696
MM-嗯。
{\fs12}Mm-hmm.{\r}

925
01:30:50,543 --> 01:30:51,739
是啊...
{\fs12}Yeah...{\r}

926
01:30:52,828 --> 01:30:55,464
是的，現在，你們所做的一切都做得很好。
{\fs12}Yeah, now, y'all done did a good job with this crop.{\r}

927
01:30:55,584 --> 01:30:57,586
 -好的，謝謝。 -嗯嗯。
{\fs12}-Well, thank you. -Mm-hmm.{\r}

928
01:30:59,251 --> 01:31:01,344
好吧，來吧，讓我們開始工作吧！
{\fs12}Well, come on, let's get to work!{\r}

929
01:31:01,464 --> 01:31:04,393
 -你確定你能做到嗎，納森？ -是的，我感覺到了！
{\fs12}-Are you sure you feel up to it, Nathan? -Yeah, I feel up to it!{\r}

930
01:31:04,513 --> 01:31:06,272
-為什麼不？ -好的。
{\fs12}-Why not? -Alright.{\r}

931
01:31:07,044 --> 01:31:08,223
來吧，騾子。
{\fs12}Come on, mule.{\r}

932
01:31:09,205 --> 01:31:11,057
嘿，快點！來吧，騾子。
{\fs12}Hey, come on! Come on, mule.{\r}

933
01:31:11,805 --> 01:31:12,808
繼續。
{\fs12}Go on.{\r}

934
01:31:30,609 --> 01:31:34,837
你知道，我很自豪你幫助你的媽媽保持這個地方的方式。
{\fs12}You know, I sure am proud of the way you helped your mama keep this place going.{\r}

935
01:31:34,957 --> 01:31:36,310
謝謝爸爸。
{\fs12}Thanks, Daddy.{\r}

936
01:31:42,951 --> 01:31:44,688
你知道，有些人，有些人...
{\fs12}You know, some people, some people...{\r}

937
01:31:44,808 --> 01:31:48,353
...可能認為這是一項艱苦的工作，但它肯定會在地獄中被打入監獄。
{\fs12}...may think this is hard work, but it sure in the hell beats going to jail.{\r}

938
01:31:49,586 --> 01:31:51,977
爸爸，你不會坐牢嗎？
{\fs12}You won't be going to jail, will you, Daddy?{\r}

939
01:31:52,097 --> 01:31:55,586
在我回到那個地方之前，他們必須殺了我。
{\fs12}They'd have to kill me before I'd go back to that place.{\r}

940
01:31:58,244 --> 01:31:59,291
來吧。
{\fs12}Come on.{\r}

941
01:32:00,273 --> 01:32:04,303
不是沒有人入獄，也不是沒有人受傷。
{\fs12}Ain't nobody going to jail, and ain't nobody getting hurt.{\r}

942
01:32:14,394 --> 01:32:17,180
現在，繼續給我一些更多的手杖。
{\fs12}Now, go on and get me some more of that cane.{\r}

943
01:32:27,262 --> 01:32:28,223
哦!
{\fs12}Oh!{\r}

944
01:32:28,343 --> 01:32:29,556
哇，騾子！
{\fs12}Whoa, mule!{\r}

945
01:32:29,676 --> 01:32:30,785
哇！哇！
{\fs12}Whoa! Whoa!{\r}

946
01:32:31,426 --> 01:32:32,451
爸爸！
{\fs12}Daddy!{\r}

947
01:32:32,571 --> 01:32:33,581
哇！哇，騾子！
{\fs12}Whoa! Whoa, mule!{\r}

948
01:32:33,701 --> 01:32:34,755
你好嗎，爸爸？
{\fs12}You alright, Daddy?{\r}

949
01:32:34,875 --> 01:32:37,211
我沒事，我沒事，只是...
{\fs12}I'm alright, I'm alright, just...{\r}

950
01:32:37,331 --> 01:32:39,880
該死的腿不會像過去那樣行事。
{\fs12}Damn leg just won't act like it used to.{\r}

951
01:32:40,719 --> 01:32:42,278
納森，你確定沒事嗎？
{\fs12}You sure you're alright, Nathan?{\r}

952
01:32:42,398 --> 01:32:44,856
是的，我會沒事的，我只需...
{\fs12}Yeah, I'll be alright, I just have to...{\r}

953
01:32:46,564 --> 01:32:48,528
我只需休息一兩分鐘。
{\fs12}I just have to rest for a minute or two.{\r}

954
01:32:48,648 --> 01:32:52,678
 -在這裡，讓我幫忙。 -不，不，你只是...留在原地。
{\fs12}-Here, let me help. -No, no, you just...stay where you is.{\r}

955
01:33:06,818 --> 01:33:08,537
你覺得好嗎，爸爸？
{\fs12}You feel alright, Daddy?{\r}

956
01:33:09,519 --> 01:33:12,402
是的，我感覺很好。太棒了
{\fs12}Yeah, I feel great. Just great.{\r}

957
01:33:14,621 --> 01:33:16,187
那雙縫...
{\fs12}...that double seam...{\r}

958
01:33:16,307 --> 01:33:19,553
...當你放手時，只需將那根手指拉開，你就明白了嗎？
{\fs12}...and when you let it go, just zip off that finger there, you got it?{\r}

959
01:33:19,673 --> 01:33:22,805
 -是的-讓我們來看看。言歸正傳。是的，就是這樣。
{\fs12}-Yeah. -Let's see. Closer. Yeah, that's it.{\r}

960
01:33:22,925 --> 01:33:26,270
好的。拉鍊，就在這裡，就在本壘板上。
{\fs12}Alright. Zip it, right in here, right over home plate.{\r}

961
01:33:28,854 --> 01:33:30,444
 -嘿！ -罷工1！
{\fs12}-Hey! -Strike 1!{\r}

962
01:33:30,872 --> 01:33:32,345
噢，來吧，喬西梅。
{\fs12}Aw, come on, Josie Mae.{\r}

963
01:33:32,465 --> 01:33:34,860
嘿，艾克！你好嗎？
{\fs12}Hey, Ike! How you doing?{\r}

964
01:33:35,479 --> 01:33:39,494
任何時候是星期六，我沒有工作要做，我做得很好。
{\fs12}Anytime it's Saturday, and I ain't got no work to do, I'm doing fine.{\r}

965
01:33:40,775 --> 01:33:42,376
 -嘿，艾克。 -嗨！
{\fs12}-Hey, Ike. -Hi!{\r}

966
01:33:42,670 --> 01:33:44,378
嘿，你到底在那裡？
{\fs12}Hey, what you got there?{\r}

967
01:33:48,320 --> 01:33:51,213
看來這封郵件今天早上到了帕金斯先生的地方...
{\fs12}It seems this piece of mail's come this morning, over to Mr. Perkins' place...{\r}

968
01:33:51,333 --> 01:33:54,597
...而且，呃...他說讓我把它帶到這裡。
{\fs12}...and, uh...he said for me to bring it over here.{\r}

969
01:33:54,717 --> 01:33:56,200
 -好吧，把它放在這裡。 -嗯嗯。
{\fs12}-Well, give it here. -Mm-mmm.{\r}

970
01:33:56,320 --> 01:33:59,793
不適合你。這是在這裡的小重要人物。
{\fs12}Ain't for you. It's for the little important man over here.{\r}

971
01:34:01,003 --> 01:34:02,241
大衛李...
{\fs12}David Lee...{\r}

972
01:34:06,461 --> 01:34:09,985
嗯，兒子，你不打算把它打開並讀給我們嗎？
{\fs12}Well, son, ain't you going to open it up and read it to us?{\r}

973
01:34:14,046 --> 01:34:16,580
好的，我現在必須走了。星期天我會在教堂看到你們。
{\fs12}OK, I've got to go now. I'll see y'all in church on Sunday.{\r}

974
01:34:16,700 --> 01:34:18,651
 -嗯嗯。 -是的，艾克，謝謝你的麻煩。
